cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use RAPTOR in your research or tooling, please cite it as below."
title: "RAPTOR: Autonomous Offensive/Defensive Research Framework"
abstract: >-
  RAPTOR is an autonomous offensive/defensive research framework built
  on top of Claude Code. It provides agentic security testing
  workflows — scan, dedup, prepare, analyse, consensus, judge, exploit,
  patch — covering static analysis (Semgrep, CodeQL), binary fuzzing
  (AFL++), web application scanning, crash root-cause analysis,
  exploitability validation, and zero-knowledge proof-of-exploit
  disclosure bundles, for defensive security research, education, and
  authorized penetration testing.
type: software
version: "3.0.0"
date-released: "2026-05-22"
license: MIT
url: "https://github.com/gadievron/raptor"
repository-code: "https://github.com/gadievron/raptor"
keywords:
  - security
  - vulnerability-research
  - static-analysis
  - fuzzing
  - codeql
  - semgrep
  - exploitability
  - llm-agents
  - claude-code
  - defensive-security
  - penetration-testing
